00:59:34,488 --> 00:59:36,573
The computer analyzes
the components...

734
00:59:36,782 --> 00:59:40,076
and the boys at the lab
duplicate the stuff down here.

735
00:59:40,661 --> 00:59:42,495
"Unknown"?

736
00:59:42,955 --> 00:59:44,497
"Unknown"?

737
01:00:01,724 --> 01:00:03,850
What the hell,
he ain't gonna smoke it.

738
01:00:09,857 --> 01:00:12,358
Mr. White can't be responsible.

739
01:00:14,612 --> 01:00:15,820
Where is he?

740
01:00:16,030 --> 01:00:17,614
Please, Mr. Stokis.

741
01:00:18,032 --> 01:00:19,741
He'll pay for this.

742
01:00:21,243 --> 01:00:22,785
Get out your wallet!

743
01:00:23,787 --> 01:00:27,040
- Good morning.
- Don't you "good morning" me.

744
01:00:28,500 --> 01:00:32,712
"Old, old relationships
suddenly seem very much the same.

745
01:00:32,880 --> 01:00:34,547
The prettiest girl in the school..."

746
01:00:36,383 --> 01:00:38,676
Is still the prettiest girl
in the school.

747
01:00:43,265 --> 01:00:46,517
- Hello?
- Hello. Oh, hi, Clark.

748
01:00:46,727 --> 01:00:51,272
Lana! Hi, I was just
thinking about you.

749
01:00:53,025 --> 01:00:55,193
Listen, I have a problem with Ricky.

750
01:00:55,361 --> 01:00:56,694
Why? What happened to Ricky?

751
01:00:56,862 --> 01:01:00,406
It's Superman's autograph you got him.
He got carried away...

752
01:01:00,574 --> 01:01:03,576
and told the kids Superman
was coming on his birthday.

753
01:01:03,827 --> 01:01:05,078
Okay, it was wrong...

754
01:01:05,245 --> 01:01:08,915
but when Wednesday comes and
Superman doesn't show, it's gonna...

755
01:01:09,917 --> 01:01:13,544
Well, Lana, in this case I think
I can go ahead and speak for Superman.

756
01:01:13,712 --> 01:01:15,797
I mean, he and I
are pretty close, you know.

757
01:01:16,006 --> 01:01:20,051
And you can tell Ricky that Superman
will be there on Wednesday, all right?

758
01:01:21,804 --> 01:01:25,223
Well, he's gonna get the best
home-cooked meal he's had...

759
01:01:25,599 --> 01:01:26,766
in a long time.

760
01:01:26,934 --> 01:01:29,936
- Tell Superman we think he's wonderful.
- All right.

761
01:01:30,104 --> 01:01:32,230
- But, Clark...
- Yeah?

762
01:01:32,606 --> 01:01:33,940
You're the best.

763
01:01:38,445 --> 01:01:41,406
And I'll take it to
the Supreme Court if I have to.

764
01:01:41,615 --> 01:01:44,909
But it wasn't our fault.
It was an act of God.

765
01:01:45,119 --> 01:01:46,911
In a church?

766
01:01:59,550 --> 01:02:00,633
Hey!

767
01:02:00,843 --> 01:02:02,802
Here's that compound you ordered.

768
01:02:02,970 --> 01:02:04,887
Can't imagine what you want with it.

769
01:02:05,055 --> 01:02:06,431
But you got it.

770
01:02:12,730 --> 01:02:15,648
What the hell am I afraid for?
I'm from Earth.

771
01:02:21,363 --> 01:02:23,489
Lana, I really wasn't expecting all this.

772
01:02:23,741 --> 01:02:26,284
I guess they did get
a little carried away.

773
01:02:40,132 --> 01:02:43,384
Superman, we all know...

774
01:02:44,011 --> 01:02:46,763
that you're not looking
for honors and awards.

775
01:02:47,598 --> 01:02:51,184
But when we heard that you were
coming to see your pal Ricky...

776
01:02:51,393 --> 01:02:55,188
we realized that this was
our chance to say thank you.

777
01:02:55,397 --> 01:02:57,774
First, for putting out
the Lake Comooga fire.

778
01:02:58,275 --> 01:03:01,527
And not least,
for saving little Ricky.

779
01:03:02,029 --> 01:03:04,697
So since you already have
the key to our hearts...

780
01:03:04,865 --> 01:03:07,033
Superman...

781
01:03:07,201 --> 01:03:11,287
may I present you
with the key to the city.

782
01:03:11,497 --> 01:03:12,872
Thank you, sir.

783
01:03:16,919 --> 01:03:18,127
Thank you.

784
01:03:34,561 --> 01:03:36,229
As you were.

785
01:03:39,233 --> 01:03:40,566
Now listen up.

786
01:03:41,068 --> 01:03:42,902
I just came in directly...

787
01:03:43,070 --> 01:03:45,238
from the Pentagon...

788
01:03:45,489 --> 01:03:49,575
and you better believe there's
a damn good reason that I did.

789
01:03:50,577 --> 01:03:52,912
Because God has given us...

790
01:03:53,080 --> 01:03:56,582
one of the greatest gifts in the world...

791
01:03:56,959 --> 01:03:58,709
Chemicals.

792
01:03:59,711 --> 01:04:04,340
Now, you people, you like to go sit
in church on Sunday, don't you?

793
01:04:04,716 --> 01:04:07,176
You like to sit and watch
the Super Bowl.

794
01:04:07,344 --> 01:04:08,427
Yeah.

795
01:04:08,595 --> 01:04:10,680
Sit on what?!

796
01:04:12,057 --> 01:04:16,269
You sit on molded, plastic seats!

797
01:04:17,062 --> 01:04:20,606
Molded to your well-fed behinds.

798
01:04:22,109 --> 01:04:26,445
Now, I don't have to tell you
that America leads the world...

799
01:04:26,613 --> 01:04:27,989
in high-grade plastics.

800
01:04:28,448 --> 01:04:32,785
We cannot afford
a chemical-plastics gap.

801
01:04:34,037 --> 01:04:35,246
Now, listen to me.

802
01:04:35,998 --> 01:04:37,623
Do you want...

803
01:04:37,791 --> 01:04:42,211
our president of the United States
sitting down...

804
01:04:43,005 --> 01:04:44,964
to write a peace treaty...

805
01:04:45,132 --> 01:04:48,050
and have his ballpoint pen bust open...

806
01:04:48,260 --> 01:04:51,470
and the ink run out all over
his nice, clean pants...

807
01:04:51,638 --> 01:04:53,472
in front of the world leaders?

808
01:04:53,640 --> 01:04:55,516
No. No.

809
01:04:56,018 --> 01:04:57,810
Now, we all know...

810
01:04:58,020 --> 01:05:02,315
that last week, half of
this great nation of ours...

811
01:05:02,566 --> 01:05:04,150
almost bit the bullet...

812
01:05:04,818 --> 01:05:07,278
if it wasn't for this man here.

813
01:05:09,448 --> 01:05:13,826
And all I can say is,
thank the Lord for Superman.

814
01:05:19,791 --> 01:05:21,918
Superman, you saved our bacon...

815
01:05:22,127 --> 01:05:24,420
and I'd like to show our gratitude.

816
01:05:27,549 --> 01:05:31,928
This is a small token
of our appreciation...

817
01:05:32,137 --> 01:05:36,766
to show to you for saving us
from a chemical-plant disaster.

818
01:05:43,023 --> 01:05:44,690
Thank you very much, general.

819
01:05:45,192 --> 01:05:47,360
This is very nice. Thank you.

820
01:05:58,789 --> 01:05:59,830
It's very nice.

821
01:06:07,214 --> 01:06:10,883
Unknown. How am I supposed
to know what "unknown" means?

822
01:06:11,134 --> 01:06:14,178
It means unknown. It means
nobody knows what it means.

823
01:06:14,346 --> 01:06:16,555
- Hello, boss?
- Gus?

824
01:06:17,057 --> 01:06:19,892
- Gus Gorman here.
- I know that. How did it go?

825
01:06:20,602 --> 01:06:24,188
You know how they're always
trying to find the secret recipe...

826
01:06:24,398 --> 01:06:26,190
in that chicken in the bucket?

827
01:06:26,400 --> 01:06:28,401
And nobody seems to know
the ingredient...

828
01:06:28,610 --> 01:06:30,736
because it's unknown, right?

829
01:06:31,405 --> 01:06:35,741
In the Kryptonite there was an unknown
element and Superman didn't die.

830
01:06:36,618 --> 01:06:38,744
He didn't die.

831
01:06:39,413 --> 01:06:42,081
I ask you to kill Superman...

832
01:06:42,249 --> 01:06:46,419
and you're telling me you couldn't
even do that one simple thing.

833
01:06:50,757 --> 01:06:51,882
Hello?

834
01:07:05,772 --> 01:07:08,357
He hasn't had
an afternoon nap for years.

835
01:07:08,567 --> 01:07:12,236
This is the biggest day of his life.
I don't know how to thank you.

836
01:07:12,404 --> 01:07:14,071
You did with that wonderful lunch.

837
01:07:14,239 --> 01:07:17,450
Oh, well, I do like to cook.

838
01:07:18,452 --> 01:07:20,453
- You'll take some coffee?
- Yes, please.

839
01:07:20,662 --> 01:07:22,788
- Decaffeinated, of course.
- Right.

840
01:07:27,794 --> 01:07:30,296
Hello? Yes.

841
01:07:31,965 --> 01:07:33,299
What?

842
01:07:33,675 --> 01:07:35,551
Oh, really?

843
01:07:35,761 --> 01:07:36,969
Yeah, he's here.

844
01:07:37,137 --> 01:07:39,138
I'll tell him.
Okay, thanks. Bye-bye.

845
01:07:39,306 --> 01:07:42,266
Superman, that was my friend Betty.

846
01:07:42,476 --> 01:07:45,978
There's an accident on the bridge.
A trailer crashed through the rail.

847
01:07:46,146 --> 01:07:49,231
It's hanging off the bridge
and the driver's in the cab.

848
01:07:49,775 --> 01:07:52,193
I'm sorry.
I hate to make you rush off.

849
01:07:52,819 --> 01:07:54,153
Well, there's no rush.

850
01:07:54,821 --> 01:07:58,574
- But the bridge...
- It's okay. I always get there on time.

851
01:07:58,784 --> 01:08:00,451
Come on, let's relax a little.

852
01:08:14,299 --> 01:08:17,802
It's unusual finding a good-looking girl
like you alone like this.

853
01:08:28,438 --> 01:08:33,359
Listen, are you sure you shouldn't
do something about the bridge?

854
01:08:34,027 --> 01:08:35,194
What bridge?

855
01:08:40,534 --> 01:08:41,659
You're right.

856
01:08:45,872 --> 01:08:47,623
I have to get going.

857
01:08:56,550 --> 01:08:58,175
Get him out of there. Come on.

858
01:08:58,385 --> 01:09:00,010
Get him out! Get him out quick!

859
01:09:00,220 --> 01:09:02,888
Come on. Get him away.
That thing's gonna go.

860
01:09:17,779 --> 01:09:19,822
Everybody okay? Joe?

861
01:09:20,574 --> 01:09:21,824
What can I do to help?

862
01:09:22,033 --> 01:09:23,534
Not much of anything now.

863
01:09:23,743 --> 01:09:26,287
If only you'd got here
a minute sooner.

864
01:10:41,655 --> 01:10:44,198
"At a special session
of the General Assembly...

865
01:10:44,366 --> 01:10:47,618
178 countries voted
to censure Superman...

866
01:10:47,786 --> 01:10:50,246
with only Colombia abstaining".

867
01:10:50,413 --> 01:10:51,914
I can tell you one thing.

868
01:10:52,123 --> 01:10:55,960
He wasn't so mean and nasty
the other day in Smallville.

869
01:10:56,169 --> 01:10:58,587
In fact, he was so full of niceness...

870
01:10:58,755 --> 01:11:01,131
I hated laying that big chunk of...

871
01:11:02,842 --> 01:11:04,843
Kryptonite. Don't you see?

872
01:11:05,011 --> 01:11:08,347
That stuff we ran off in the lab
wasn't a complete failure after all.

873
01:11:08,515 --> 01:11:11,392
Right after Gus gave it to him,
he started to turn into...

874
01:11:11,601 --> 01:11:13,686
an ornery, evil, malicious, selfish...

875
01:11:13,895 --> 01:11:15,813
- A normal person.
- Yes.

876
01:11:16,398 --> 01:11:19,942
And now that Superman
is out of the nice-guy business...

877
01:11:20,110 --> 01:11:21,819
We can get to work on that oil.

878
01:11:45,552 --> 01:11:49,722
And now, the supreme
moment, as the last runner...

879
01:11:49,889 --> 01:11:53,851
the one given the great honor
of lighting the ceremonial flame...

880
01:11:54,019 --> 01:11:58,147
runs the last leg of a marathon
that began seven days ago...

881
01:11:58,356 --> 01:12:03,068
as this torch has been passed
from athlete to athlete...

882
01:12:03,278 --> 01:12:06,030
for 970 miles...

883
01:12:06,197 --> 01:12:08,032
across the country.

884
01:12:49,199 --> 01:12:52,493
How can he say that pure categories
have no objective meaning...

885
01:12:52,702 --> 01:12:55,537
in transcendental logic?
What about synthetic unity?

886
01:12:58,416 --> 01:13:00,167
Hi, honey! Am I in your way?

887
01:13:00,335 --> 01:13:03,295
- Stick around, you may learn something.
- Hi, Lorelei.

888
01:13:03,463 --> 01:13:07,132
All the oil tankers in the world
are totally controlled by computers.

889
01:13:07,300 --> 01:13:10,177
They tell them where to go,
how much oil to pick up...

890
01:13:10,387 --> 01:13:12,096
and where to deliver it.

891
01:13:12,263 --> 01:13:14,139
Don't they have captains
on these ships?

892
01:13:14,307 --> 01:13:15,766
Yes, but they don't need them.

893
01:13:15,934 --> 01:13:19,228
That's a throwback to some
sentimental, seafaring baloney.

894
01:13:19,396 --> 01:13:23,107
You will command the tankers
to sail toward a 50-mile area...

895
01:13:23,274 --> 01:13:25,150
in the middle of the Atlantic Ocean.

896
01:13:25,318 --> 01:13:26,985
And do what?

897
01:13:27,153 --> 01:13:29,363
And do nothing.

898
01:13:29,572 --> 01:13:31,824
Just sit there.

899
01:13:32,992 --> 01:13:35,869
How are all the people
gonna get their oil?

900
01:13:37,038 --> 01:13:39,456
You catch on fast, old buddy.

901
01:13:42,168 --> 01:13:45,337
Every oil pump in America is run by...

902
01:13:45,547 --> 01:13:48,298
- Computers. I know.
- Will you stop interrupting?!

903
01:13:48,508 --> 01:13:49,675
I'm sorry.

904
01:13:50,009 --> 01:13:53,804
You will command the pumps
to stop pumping.

905
01:13:53,972 --> 01:13:57,891
Then I want you to program
one special command...

906
01:13:58,101 --> 01:14:00,185
into all these systems.

907
01:14:00,353 --> 01:14:03,147
Tell them these orders
are irreversible.

908
01:14:03,356 --> 01:14:07,109
So it would be impossible
for anybody to switch them back.

909
01:14:07,318 --> 01:14:09,194
Can you do this for me, old buddy?

910
01:14:09,737 --> 01:14:11,613
Old pal?

911
01:14:18,955 --> 01:14:21,373
You know, you get your way
all the time.

912
01:14:22,542 --> 01:14:24,334
And it's not right.

913
01:14:26,754 --> 01:14:28,881
I wanna know when I get a taste.

914
01:14:35,346 --> 01:14:39,600
I think you've already had
a taste of freedom, haven't you?

915
01:14:39,809 --> 01:14:42,352
Or would you prefer jail?

916
01:14:42,562 --> 01:14:44,396
You can't run that jail number on me.

917
01:14:44,731 --> 01:14:48,317
Because I know I mean more to you
out here doing things for you...

918
01:14:48,526 --> 01:14:51,236
than sitting in jail
doing nothing for nobody.

919
01:14:52,989 --> 01:14:54,072
I see.

920
01:14:54,240 --> 01:14:56,074
What do you want?

921
01:15:02,415 --> 01:15:04,875
What? A waste basket?

922
01:15:05,084 --> 01:15:07,211
No. These are plans.

923
01:15:08,087 --> 01:15:09,588
Blueprints.

924
01:15:10,131 --> 01:15:12,216
- For what?
- A computer.

925
01:15:12,383 --> 01:15:15,219
- We've already got computers.
- No, not like this.

926
01:15:15,386 --> 01:15:18,931
There's not a computer like this
in the whole world anyplace.

927
01:15:19,474 --> 01:15:21,350
It doesn't exist. You see...

928
01:15:21,643 --> 01:15:22,935
we have to build it.

929
01:15:23,478 --> 01:15:24,561
What will it do?

930
01:15:24,896 --> 01:15:26,730
Anything I tell it.

931
01:15:27,273 --> 01:15:29,441
What will it do for me?

932
01:15:29,609 --> 01:15:33,904
For you? It will do anything you
tell me to tell it to do for you.

933
01:15:34,155 --> 01:15:35,489
Wow.

934
01:15:40,286 --> 01:15:41,870
Tell me.

935
01:15:43,790 --> 01:15:47,084
First of all, if anyone attacks
this machine or anything...

936
01:15:47,293 --> 01:15:49,169
the computer counterattacks it.

937
01:15:49,379 --> 01:15:52,381
I mean, it finds their weaknesses
and wipes them out.

938
01:15:52,882 --> 01:15:53,966
Right, old buddy.

939
01:15:54,175 --> 01:15:57,970
You deal with my oil
and I'll build you your machine.

940
01:16:01,641 --> 01:16:03,308
Okay, I'll do it.

941
01:16:03,476 --> 01:16:07,020
But I'm not so sure about
this irreversible business.

942
01:16:24,163 --> 01:16:26,832
They all kind of went...
What the hell?

943
01:16:30,253 --> 01:16:32,713
That's it. The last tanker.

944
01:16:33,423 --> 01:16:36,341
They're all mine now. All mine.

945
01:16:36,884 --> 01:16:38,385
Yay.

946
01:16:38,595 --> 01:16:40,846
Not quite.

947
01:16:41,014 --> 01:16:43,515
What's that in
the upper-middle quadrant?

948
01:16:44,517 --> 01:16:46,018
It's a tanker.

949
01:16:48,146 --> 01:16:50,063
And it's going the wrong way.

950
01:17:00,867 --> 01:17:02,034
Skipper?

951
01:17:02,201 --> 01:17:04,870
There it is again.
"Proceed immediately to...

952
01:17:05,079 --> 01:17:08,165
latitude 30 north, longitude 45 west.

953
01:17:09,876 --> 01:17:11,543
There await further orders".

954
01:17:11,711 --> 01:17:13,879
Hell, that's the middle of the Atlantic.

955
01:17:14,047 --> 01:17:16,965
I'm not taking my ship there
just to await further orders...

956
01:17:17,175 --> 01:17:18,717
no matter what that says.

957
01:17:18,926 --> 01:17:22,554
We're supposed to go to Metropolis,
and we're going to Metropolis.

958
01:17:22,722 --> 01:17:24,014
All right.

959
01:17:36,402 --> 01:17:37,736
That's where she is. Yeah.

960
01:17:37,904 --> 01:17:39,988
Come on, get it up there.

961
01:17:41,407 --> 01:17:42,783
Miss?

962
01:17:43,326 --> 01:17:45,577
Miss, can you hear me?

963
01:17:45,745 --> 01:17:48,413
Listen, we are here to help you.

964
01:17:48,623 --> 01:17:52,084
Don't jump. I repeat, do not jump!

965
01:17:53,711 --> 01:17:55,087
Thought you'd never get here.

966
01:17:55,963 --> 01:17:58,715
Don't expect me to save you.
I don't do that anymore.

967
01:17:58,925 --> 01:18:00,008
Don't worry.

968
01:18:00,176 --> 01:18:02,928
I'm long past saving.

969
01:18:07,809 --> 01:18:09,267
Well...

970
01:18:09,936 --> 01:18:11,770
don't let me keep you
from anything.

971
01:18:12,438 --> 01:18:14,022
I'm not in a rush.

972
01:18:19,862 --> 01:18:21,822
What did you have in mind?

973
01:18:22,198 --> 01:18:23,782
Lots of things.

974
01:18:23,950 --> 01:18:25,242
Oh, yeah?

975
01:18:28,329 --> 01:18:31,248
If you'll just do me
one little favor first.

976
01:18:31,457 --> 01:18:32,791
What's that?

977
01:18:33,292 --> 01:18:35,043
Well...

978
01:18:35,586 --> 01:18:37,796
See, there's this little boat...

979
01:18:38,005 --> 01:18:41,717
and it's not going where
it's supposed to go and...

980
01:19:18,337 --> 01:19:20,005
Stop all engines!

981
01:19:21,007 --> 01:19:22,674
Stop all engines!

982
01:20:16,062 --> 01:20:17,562
Hi.

983
01:20:33,120 --> 01:20:35,539
How about a little aprčs-ski?

984
01:20:46,509 --> 01:20:47,926
Champagne?

985
01:21:11,701 --> 01:21:13,535
Take your turn like everybody else!

986
01:21:13,744 --> 01:21:15,787
Stop it!

987
01:21:18,541 --> 01:21:20,584
He's coming over here, Martha.

988
01:21:24,130 --> 01:21:25,547
Don't you do that!

989
01:21:27,133 --> 01:21:29,217
Don't! Please!

990
01:21:35,433 --> 01:21:37,392
Hit him with your handbag!

991
01:21:40,980 --> 01:21:44,316
Help me! Please, help me.
Somebody's beating up my husband.

992
01:21:44,483 --> 01:21:48,111
- I've gotta call the police.
- Jack, go with her, okay?

993
01:21:49,155 --> 01:21:51,656
The third one today,
and at night it's worse.

994
01:21:51,866 --> 01:21:53,658
Somebody's behind this.

995
01:21:53,868 --> 01:21:55,619
You can't tell me there's no oil.

996
01:21:55,786 --> 01:21:58,163
You can't say someone's
not getting rich off this.

997
01:21:58,372 --> 01:22:00,206
Someone's always getting rich.

998
01:22:00,416 --> 01:22:02,417
You know who suffers? The small guy.

999
01:22:02,627 --> 01:22:05,837
The East Coast gets
the brunt of the spill.

1000
01:22:48,547 --> 01:22:51,091
No, I cannot go out with you tonight.

1001
01:22:51,550 --> 01:22:53,093
No. I'm busy tomorrow night too.

1002
01:22:53,260 --> 01:22:55,053
Oh, yeah? Doing what?

1003
01:22:55,471 --> 01:22:57,305
I'll think of something. Look...

1004
01:22:57,515 --> 01:23:00,684
- I gotta go. Ricky needs me.
- Lana.

1005
01:23:00,851 --> 01:23:03,979
Brad, please stop calling me.
I've told you!

1006
01:23:04,146 --> 01:23:06,231
Well, you listen to me, huh?

1007
01:23:06,399 --> 01:23:08,400
You better start appreciating old Brad.

1008
01:23:08,818 --> 01:23:10,360
What else you got in Smallville?

1009
01:23:16,283 --> 01:23:18,827
What else have I got in Smallville?

1010
01:23:20,371 --> 01:23:22,372
I think I got the right answer.

1011
01:23:23,040 --> 01:23:24,416
So do I.

1012
01:23:33,509 --> 01:23:37,220
Smallville Airport, what flights
do you have to Metropolis tomorrow?

1013
01:23:42,852 --> 01:23:45,395
- Where do I put this?
- Over there.

1014
01:23:47,106 --> 01:23:50,150
- Where do you want this?
- Put it up there.

1015
01:23:53,446 --> 01:23:56,281
Are you kidding? I'm not going in there.

1016
01:24:17,303 --> 01:24:19,637
Hey, hey. Come on.

1017
01:24:28,147 --> 01:24:29,314
Just leave him alone.

1018
01:24:51,087 --> 01:24:53,213
I can't get through.
Something's happening.

1019
01:24:53,422 --> 01:24:55,215
Hey, look! Superman's drunk!

1020
01:24:55,424 --> 01:24:58,510
- I wanna see what's happening here.
- Ricky. Ricky!

1021
01:24:59,095 --> 01:25:02,013
- Ricky.
- Yeah, that's right.

1022
01:25:02,556 --> 01:25:04,849
- Thank you.
- It's a disgrace, that's what it is.

1023
01:25:05,017 --> 01:25:07,852
I'll tell you, nobody's ever
gonna trust that creep again.

1024
01:25:08,020 --> 01:25:09,479
He's washed up.

1025
01:25:12,983 --> 01:25:15,693
What are you looking at? Huh?

1026
01:25:16,070 --> 01:25:19,280
Excuse me. Superman? It's me, Ricky.

1027
01:25:19,490 --> 01:25:21,157
Ricky from Smallville.

1028
01:25:21,367 --> 01:25:23,118
Tell them you won't hurt anybody!

1029
01:25:23,327 --> 01:25:24,494
He's changed.

1030
01:25:24,662 --> 01:25:27,330
No! Maybe he's just sick.

1031
01:25:27,540 --> 01:25:29,374
Superman, please get better!

1032
01:25:29,583 --> 01:25:31,042
He's not listening to you.

1033
01:25:31,210 --> 01:25:35,046
Yes, he is. He can hear me.
He's got super-hearing.

1034
01:25:35,214 --> 01:25:37,841
Superman, you're just in a slump!

1035
01:25:38,008 --> 01:25:39,759
You'll be great again!

1036
01:25:39,969 --> 01:25:41,469
You can do it, Superman!

1037
01:25:41,679 --> 01:25:44,639
Superman, you can hear me, can't you?

1038
01:25:44,849 --> 01:25:47,392
Superman, you're just in a slump.

1039
01:25:47,560 --> 01:25:51,187
You'll be great again.
You can do it, superman.

1040
01:25:51,355 --> 01:25:54,399
Superman, you can hear me, can't you?

1041
01:26:14,587 --> 01:26:15,628
He's gone nuts!

1042
01:26:17,506 --> 01:26:18,548
Come on!

1043
01:27:45,511 --> 01:27:47,470
I can give as good as I get.

1044
01:27:48,597 --> 01:27:51,599
Oh, yeah? All right, come on! Come on!

1045
01:27:51,767 --> 01:27:53,518
Come on! Come on!

1046
01:28:19,003 --> 01:28:21,629
What's the matter, Kent?
Too warm for you, huh?

1047
01:28:23,757 --> 01:28:26,551
Come on, chicken! Come and get me.

1048
01:28:26,719 --> 01:28:29,012
You've been on my nerves a long time!

1049
01:28:50,909 --> 01:28:52,994
You always wanted to fly, Kent.

1050
01:28:53,203 --> 01:28:54,412
Now's your chance.

1051
01:33:48,540 --> 01:33:50,041
Skipper!

1052
01:34:04,681 --> 01:34:07,058
God, would you look at that!

1053
01:34:54,481 --> 01:34:57,108
Miss Lorelei Ambrosia
isn't at home right now.

1054
01:34:57,317 --> 01:34:59,527
But if you'd care to leave a message...

1055
01:34:59,736 --> 01:35:03,114
why not deliver it to her in person?

1056
01:35:03,281 --> 01:35:06,659
So you've finally shown
your true colors.

1057
01:35:06,868 --> 01:35:11,122
Well, if you're looking for us,
here's where you'll find us.

1058
01:35:11,331 --> 01:35:13,040
Do drop in.

1059
01:35:19,631 --> 01:35:21,298
Wow, this is fun!

1060
01:35:21,717 --> 01:35:23,759
Fun? The fun's just starting.

1061
01:35:24,344 --> 01:35:27,179
Wait till Superman finds us,
then you'll see some fun.

1062
01:35:27,389 --> 01:35:29,765
Wait, you gonna mess with Superman?

1063
01:35:30,058 --> 01:35:34,061
Let's go. I want to be ready for him
when he falls into our trap.

1064
01:35:34,354 --> 01:35:38,190
I just don't see why you can't
balloon down like the rest of us.

1065
01:35:38,400 --> 01:35:39,483
Well...

1066
01:35:41,319 --> 01:35:42,445
No way.

1067
01:35:42,654 --> 01:35:45,156
I just don't believe a man can fly.

1068
01:36:02,340 --> 01:36:04,341
Watch out, horsy!

1069
01:36:14,060 --> 01:36:16,187
Don't, don't, don't.

1070
01:36:16,354 --> 01:36:18,773
Just don't try to fly.

1071
01:36:19,024 --> 01:36:20,483
Don't try to fly!

1072
01:36:33,705 --> 01:36:36,165
Will you get out of my way!

1073
01:36:54,976 --> 01:36:57,311
- Hurry! Hurry up!
- I am hurrying.

1074
01:37:02,901 --> 01:37:05,194
- I can't see anything.
- Turn on the light.

1075
01:37:05,362 --> 01:37:08,113
- Where's the light switch?
- Where do you usually find it?

1076
01:37:08,323 --> 01:37:10,616
I don't know.
I guess I'll check the doorway.

1077
01:37:10,826 --> 01:37:14,703
God, it's pitch-black in here.
Oh, that's better.

1078
01:37:18,166 --> 01:37:20,918
Wow, what a jukebox!

1079
01:37:21,086 --> 01:37:23,045
I told you, didn't I?

1080
01:37:23,213 --> 01:37:25,506
There. The ultimate computer!

1081
01:37:32,681 --> 01:37:36,433
It does everything a computer can do
and 1000 things none of them can do.

1082
01:37:36,643 --> 01:37:38,060
Let's give it a dry run.

1083
01:37:38,270 --> 01:37:40,187
Wait a minute.
We've gotta wait for Gus.

1084
01:37:40,397 --> 01:37:41,689
Who needs Gus?

1085
01:37:41,857 --> 01:37:45,234
- He's the only one who can operate it.
- Like fish he is!

1086
01:37:45,443 --> 01:37:48,654
I know enough about computers
to put a PhD to shame.

1087
01:37:48,864 --> 01:37:51,407
Come now, brother dear,
you didn't think...

1088
01:37:51,575 --> 01:37:54,285
I was gonna let that little man
run the show, did you?

1089
01:37:54,661 --> 01:37:56,704
Why don't peons tidy up
when they're done?

1090
01:37:56,913 --> 01:37:59,707
Come on, Bubba, it's showtime.

1091
01:38:03,128 --> 01:38:05,796
Engage those buttons
to activate the alpha circuit...

1092
01:38:06,006 --> 01:38:07,381
and lock the modular grid.

1093
01:38:07,591 --> 01:38:12,469
You! Activate circuits 29 through W-7...

1094
01:38:12,679 --> 01:38:16,765
and start full-power coordinates
on exterior defensive systems.

1095
01:38:16,975 --> 01:38:19,852
In other words, push this red button.

1096
01:38:20,687 --> 01:38:22,688
How did you know about that?

1097
01:38:40,624 --> 01:38:41,665
He's here!

1098
01:38:41,833 --> 01:38:44,835
Good. Let's give him
something to worry about.

1099
01:38:45,921 --> 01:38:47,379
Now, let's see...

1100
01:38:47,839 --> 01:38:50,215
Tracking systems locked.

1101
01:39:15,700 --> 01:39:17,701
Let the games begin.

1102
01:39:18,703 --> 01:39:20,329
Don't tense up now, honey.

1103
01:39:52,862 --> 01:39:55,739
Come on, Bubba,
you're wasting your rockets.

1104
01:40:03,164 --> 01:40:05,249
Come on, Superman!

1105
01:40:06,334 --> 01:40:08,210
Let him have it, Ross.

1106
01:40:15,093 --> 01:40:16,927
Bubba, keep firing.

1107
01:40:17,095 --> 01:40:19,763
Keep him occupied
while I get the MX ready.

1108
01:40:47,000 --> 01:40:49,209
What the hell is going on?

1109
01:40:57,302 --> 01:41:00,971
You keep your rockets coming.
He won't notice the missile till too late!

1110
01:41:09,147 --> 01:41:11,315
So much for your catlike reflexes.

1111
01:41:21,785 --> 01:41:23,368
Oh, God!

1112
01:41:33,338 --> 01:41:36,298
No more. Look, you sit.

1113
01:41:36,508 --> 01:41:38,300
Sit, sit!

1114
01:41:42,013 --> 01:41:43,138
Help!

1115
01:41:43,848 --> 01:41:47,017
Hello? Forget you, jackass!

1116
01:41:48,269 --> 01:41:49,603
That's him out of the way.

1117
01:41:49,771 --> 01:41:53,857
Sis, how would you like to control
all the world's weapons systems?

1118
01:41:54,734 --> 01:41:55,943
Baby!

1119
01:41:56,152 --> 01:41:57,611
It's Daddy!

1120
01:41:58,696 --> 01:42:00,864
Hey, what are you doing with my baby?

1121
01:42:01,324 --> 01:42:05,494
Gus, old buddy, genius.
Come up and join the fun.

1122
01:42:16,381 --> 01:42:19,967
He's still coming.
Arm the inner defenses.

1123
01:42:24,389 --> 01:42:25,889
All right, the game's over.

1124
01:42:26,558 --> 01:42:27,599
Hi, honey.

1125
01:42:28,143 --> 01:42:29,309
I don't know you, lady.

1126
01:42:31,354 --> 01:42:32,563
But the other night...

1127
01:42:35,191 --> 01:42:37,401
I'm sorry, but that wasn't me.

1128
01:42:37,569 --> 01:42:38,902
That guy's gone.

1129
01:42:40,697 --> 01:42:42,156
And you're next, Webster.

1130
01:42:43,283 --> 01:42:46,702
Never underestimate
the power of computers.

1131
01:42:46,995 --> 01:42:48,328
How do you like it?

1132
01:42:48,538 --> 01:42:51,081
I think it's typical
of people like you, Webster.

1133
01:42:51,374 --> 01:42:54,751
Instead of helping others, the four
of you just wanna help yourselves.

1134
01:42:54,919 --> 01:42:57,254
Four of you?

1135
01:42:57,422 --> 01:42:59,548
You mean, us? Four? Wait...

1136
01:42:59,757 --> 01:43:01,425
Hey, man!

1137
01:43:01,593 --> 01:43:05,262
That's only his last name.
He likes to be called "Superman".

1138
01:43:06,055 --> 01:43:08,682
See, I'm not with them, Superman.

1139
01:43:09,267 --> 01:43:10,684
You could've fooled me, mister.

1140
01:43:19,027 --> 01:43:20,527
That's very good.

1141
01:43:22,989 --> 01:43:26,491
Let's see how long
he can carry on without any air.

1142
01:43:48,640 --> 01:43:50,599
He's still coming!
He's going to get me!

1143
01:43:50,767 --> 01:43:51,892
Don't bet on it!

1144
01:44:04,572 --> 01:44:05,948
You're hurting him.

1145
01:44:10,036 --> 01:44:12,120
- That's Kryptonite!
- Yes.

1146
01:44:12,288 --> 01:44:14,831
- This time we got it right!
- You're a genius.

1147
01:44:15,375 --> 01:44:18,961
You've invented a machine
that can find anybody's weak spot.

1148
01:44:19,462 --> 01:44:21,004
Congratulations, old buddy.

1149
01:44:21,172 --> 01:44:24,424
You'll go down in history
as the man who killed Superman!

1150
01:44:24,634 --> 01:44:25,842
I'm... No.

1151
01:44:26,552 --> 01:44:27,844
Superman!

1152
01:44:28,012 --> 01:44:29,596
No!

1153
01:44:30,139 --> 01:44:32,432
- Where do you think you're going?
- Never mind.

1154
01:44:32,600 --> 01:44:35,519
- Turn the power up.
- Hasn't he had enough?

1155
01:44:39,357 --> 01:44:40,649
Turn it up!

1156
01:44:40,817 --> 01:44:42,943
Power! More power!

1157
01:45:04,382 --> 01:45:07,050
Seventy-five. Current 7.75.

1158
01:45:11,139 --> 01:45:15,892
There's a current level of 7
that is not supposed to be on bar...

1159
01:45:16,102 --> 01:45:17,686
Oh, here it is!

1160
01:45:44,339 --> 01:45:45,380
What's going on?

1161
01:45:46,257 --> 01:45:48,091
I don't know. The power's gone.

1162
01:45:48,551 --> 01:45:50,427
Gus must have pulled the plug out.

1163
01:45:50,928 --> 01:45:52,387
It worked.

1164
01:45:52,597 --> 01:45:54,931
It worked! I got it!

1165
01:45:58,936 --> 01:46:00,437
What have you got?

1166
01:46:02,940 --> 01:46:04,691
- Give me that screw.
- This screw?

1167
01:46:04,901 --> 01:46:07,027
- That screw.
- Never!

1168
01:46:11,449 --> 01:46:13,950
Hey, wait. I can't see.

1169
01:46:36,516 --> 01:46:37,641
What?

1170
01:46:40,478 --> 01:46:41,937
Holy!

1171
01:46:42,480 --> 01:46:44,648
No! Make it stop!

1172
01:46:46,275 --> 01:46:47,734
I can't! It's out of control!

1173
01:46:47,944 --> 01:46:51,113
But how? Where's it getting
the power from?

1174
01:46:54,659 --> 01:46:56,868
It's feeding itself.

1175
01:46:57,078 --> 01:46:58,328
It wants to live!

1176
01:47:21,227 --> 01:47:23,395
It's this thing here. We'll go to the zoo.

1177
01:47:23,604 --> 01:47:26,857
I'll do that tomorrow,
and then we'll go on to the...

1178
01:47:27,984 --> 01:47:30,527
- What's happening?
- It's okay, Ricky.

1179
01:47:30,778 --> 01:47:31,945
Put the lights on!

1180
01:47:51,883 --> 01:47:53,925
Stop it! You're killing him!

1181
01:47:55,720 --> 01:47:57,095
Stop it!

1182
01:48:09,567 --> 01:48:10,984
Hey. Put me down!

1183
01:48:28,252 --> 01:48:31,338
Don't leave us alone in here! Superman!

1184
01:48:35,676 --> 01:48:36,801
Oh, I get it.

1185
01:48:36,969 --> 01:48:40,555
The coaxial energy shaft is engaging
the grid source factor. Right.

1186
01:48:40,765 --> 01:48:42,599
We're through, frogface.
I'm splitting.

1187
01:48:42,767 --> 01:48:44,351
Hey, wait a minute!

1188
01:48:46,896 --> 01:48:49,564
Girls. Girls, come out of there!

1189
01:48:59,200 --> 01:49:01,451
Help me! Please!

1190
01:49:08,125 --> 01:49:09,251
Sis?

1191
01:49:13,089 --> 01:49:14,381
Oh, my God.

1192
01:49:21,973 --> 01:49:23,265
What is that?

1193
01:49:34,860 --> 01:49:36,111
Lorelei!

1194
01:49:38,656 --> 01:49:40,824
Sis, it's your Bubba!

1195
01:50:18,863 --> 01:50:20,530
Help me. Help!

1196
01:50:22,742 --> 01:50:24,034
Superman!

1197
01:50:27,121 --> 01:50:28,204
Honey!

1198
01:50:28,372 --> 01:50:32,250
Honey, I'm stuck here! Help!
What about me?

1199
01:50:43,387 --> 01:50:44,429
Look out!

1200
01:52:53,768 --> 01:52:54,976
Bubba?

1201
01:53:41,315 --> 01:53:43,066
Thank you, brother.

1202
01:53:50,074 --> 01:53:51,783
Regular or premium?

1203
01:53:51,992 --> 01:53:56,079
She hasn't had a drink in so long,
give her a tankful of the good stuff.

1204
01:53:57,998 --> 01:53:59,040
How you doing?

1205
01:53:59,208 --> 01:54:02,293
Please don't talk to me.
I'm having enough trouble hanging on.

1206
01:54:02,503 --> 01:54:05,255
Okay, we'll go slow.
You're perfectly safe.

1207
01:54:05,881 --> 01:54:07,298
I'm not gonna argue with you.

1208
01:54:07,466 --> 01:54:10,593
I mean, any man who can trick
my machine can do anything.

1209
01:54:10,761 --> 01:54:12,470
How did you beat my defenses?

1210
01:54:12,680 --> 01:54:16,099
Those defenses are good as long
as it didn't know it's in trouble.

1211
01:54:16,308 --> 01:54:19,811
This time it didn't see the danger.
I went in with plain old acid.

1212
01:54:20,020 --> 01:54:23,648
It didn't know that when acid gets hot,
it'll eat through anything.

1213
01:54:24,191 --> 01:54:25,775
- Watch the trees.
- Whoa!

1214
01:54:26,360 --> 01:54:29,445
I guess it died of acid indigestion.

1215
01:54:30,698 --> 01:54:33,283
But what's gonna happen
to Ross and the ladies?

1216
01:54:33,450 --> 01:54:36,995
They're gonna have to see the police.
It's not your problem anymore.

1217
01:54:38,539 --> 01:54:40,081
Are we in Metropolis yet?

1218
01:54:40,291 --> 01:54:43,376
Nope. We're just gonna make
a little stop right over there.

1219
01:54:51,051 --> 01:54:53,595
We're on the ground, Gus.
Morning.

1220
01:54:53,762 --> 01:54:55,763
- You okay, Supe?
- I'm fine.

1221
01:54:55,973 --> 01:54:57,140
Excuse me a second.

1222
01:55:01,478 --> 01:55:03,271
Can you guys spare one of these?

1223
01:55:04,148 --> 01:55:06,858
- Sure, Superman.
- It is Superman, isn't it?

1224
01:55:07,067 --> 01:55:09,068
Are you kidding? Is that?

1225
01:55:09,278 --> 01:55:11,988
Didn't you see us fly out of the sky?

1226
01:55:13,198 --> 01:55:17,785
We're the only two men who can fly.
"Is it Superman?"

1227
01:55:17,995 --> 01:55:19,495
Just right.

1228
01:55:20,331 --> 01:55:21,372
Okay, Gus, let's go.

1229
01:55:21,582 --> 01:55:24,667
I was afraid you'd say that.
I thought I'd take the bus.

1230
01:55:25,169 --> 01:55:28,504
Well, suit yourself.
Does your boss have a computer here?

1231
01:55:28,839 --> 01:55:31,758
Yeah, he got a little bitty one
about that big.

1232
01:55:31,926 --> 01:55:35,595
You tell him he can do a lot worse
than to give Gus Gorman here a job.

1233
01:55:37,848 --> 01:55:39,432
Wow, thank you, Supe.

1234
01:55:39,767 --> 01:55:40,808
Take care.

1235
01:55:42,686 --> 01:55:44,187
I'll see you around.

1236
01:55:50,277 --> 01:55:51,361
So long.

1237
01:55:54,406 --> 01:55:56,115
Take it easy, man.

1238
01:55:57,493 --> 01:56:01,704
Well, you got good references,
so if you want that job...

1239
01:56:05,751 --> 01:56:08,544
Nah, this is not for me.
I think I'll take that bus.

1240
01:56:08,712 --> 01:56:10,630
Can you tell me
where the bus station is?

1241
01:56:10,839 --> 01:56:13,424
Yeah, about nine, 10 miles over there.

1242
01:56:13,634 --> 01:56:18,096
Nine or 10 miles. Okay.

1243
01:56:18,263 --> 01:56:20,348
Hey. You really flew with him?

1244
01:56:20,516 --> 01:56:23,559
Superman? Have you ever
seen Superman before?

1245
01:56:25,562 --> 01:56:26,604
No.

1246
01:56:26,897 --> 01:56:30,400
Oh, you don't know about me and him?
Me and Superman?

1247
01:56:35,572 --> 01:56:37,907
Yeah, we go way back together.

1248
01:56:38,075 --> 01:56:40,743
We always, usually, sometimes, we...

1249
01:56:42,204 --> 01:56:43,955
Nine or 10 miles?

1250
01:56:44,498 --> 01:56:46,416
I think I'll walk.

1251
01:56:46,792 --> 01:56:48,209
Yeah, I'll walk.

1252
01:56:48,794 --> 01:56:50,003
Yeah.

1253
01:56:55,050 --> 01:56:56,259
Clark.

1254
01:56:56,593 --> 01:56:59,595
What a nice surprise! Come in.

1255
01:56:59,763 --> 01:57:01,347
- Gosh. Hi, Mr. Kent.
- Hi, Ricky.

1256
01:57:01,515 --> 01:57:04,017
- Guess who Mom's having dinner with.
- Who?

1257
01:57:04,226 --> 01:57:05,601
Superman!

1258
01:57:06,145 --> 01:57:08,354
Yeah, that's what I came to tell you.

1259
01:57:08,564 --> 01:57:10,440
Superman said to tell you he's sorry...

1260
01:57:10,649 --> 01:57:14,318
but he's run into a problem and he
won't be able to have dinner with you.

1261
01:57:14,486 --> 01:57:16,779
- I guess he misses a lot of dinners.
- Yeah.

1262
01:57:17,948 --> 01:57:19,824
Would you mind settling for me?

1263
01:57:20,034 --> 01:57:21,284
Any day.

1264
01:57:22,161 --> 01:57:23,494
- I'll get my things.
- Okay.

1265
01:57:25,414 --> 01:57:28,916
You know, Lana, I was talking
to Superman the other day.

1266
01:57:29,126 --> 01:57:32,879
You know, he and I, we talk a lot.

1267
01:57:33,380 --> 01:57:36,716
And he felt badly about you having
to pawn your diamond ring.

1268
01:57:39,803 --> 01:57:41,304
Well, he found...

1269
01:57:42,514 --> 01:57:45,725
He found this one just lying around.

1270
01:57:47,019 --> 01:57:49,479
He wanted you to have this.

1271
01:57:56,320 --> 01:57:58,279
Wow, a ring from Superman!

1272
01:57:59,448 --> 01:58:01,240
- It's okay. I got it.
- Sorry.

1273
01:58:01,408 --> 01:58:02,825
Look at that.

1274
01:58:03,660 --> 01:58:05,995
- Oh, Clark.
- It's okay.

1275
01:58:06,205 --> 01:58:07,497
It fits.

1276
01:58:07,998 --> 01:58:09,332
It looks really pretty.

1277
01:58:09,500 --> 01:58:10,875
Thank you.

1278
01:58:11,919 --> 01:58:13,586
Well...

1279
01:58:13,754 --> 01:58:14,837
- Brad.
- Brad.

1280
01:58:15,297 --> 01:58:16,339
Son of a bitch.

1281
01:58:18,175 --> 01:58:20,093
Kent, I hate you.

1282
01:58:21,011 --> 01:58:22,929
I've always hated you.

1283
01:58:23,472 --> 01:58:25,223
- You know why?
- No.

1284
01:58:25,390 --> 01:58:27,016
- Because you're nice.
- Not really.

1285
01:58:27,226 --> 01:58:28,684
And nice guys finish last.

1286
01:58:40,489 --> 01:58:42,115
Lois, I've got to hand it to you.

1287
01:58:42,324 --> 01:58:44,700
Who else could turn
a vacation into a story...

1288
01:58:44,910 --> 01:58:47,870
that'll blow the lid off
of corruption in the Caribbean?

1289
01:58:48,080 --> 01:58:51,374
I knew I was on to something
when that taxi driver kidnapped me.

1290
01:58:51,583 --> 01:58:53,584
Lois, you're terrific.

1291
01:58:53,794 --> 01:58:57,171
I have to be. Seems I've got
some new competition.

1292
01:58:59,091 --> 01:59:01,634
The story that you wrote
on the class reunion?

1293
01:59:01,844 --> 01:59:03,636
- I thought it was terrific.
- Thanks.

1294
01:59:03,804 --> 01:59:07,431
And fascinating. I liked the part
about the little girl back home.

1295
01:59:07,599 --> 01:59:09,892
I'll take you to lunch
and you tell me about it.

1296
01:59:10,727 --> 01:59:14,021
I'd love to, but I'm having lunch
with Mr. White's new secretary.

1297
01:59:14,189 --> 01:59:15,231
- Hi, Lana.
- Hi, Clark.

1298
01:59:15,399 --> 01:59:19,735
Lana. Lois, say hello to Lana Lang,
Smallville's newest gift to Metropolis.

1299
01:59:19,903 --> 01:59:22,363
I'm glad to meet you.
I like your writing a lot.

1300
01:59:22,739 --> 01:59:23,823
Thank you.

1301
01:59:24,783 --> 01:59:26,117
I like your sparkler a lot.

1302
01:59:26,326 --> 01:59:29,245
Me too. I couldn't believe it
when Clark gave it to me.

1303
01:59:30,747 --> 01:59:32,874
- Clark gave it to you?
- Yes.

1304
01:59:35,586 --> 01:59:36,961
Mr. White.

1305
01:59:37,171 --> 01:59:40,298
Mr. White, look what I've got for you.

1306
01:59:40,507 --> 01:59:43,426
People, I am in love with this machine!

1307
01:59:43,594 --> 01:59:48,222
Mr. White, excuse me, but I have
a couple of errands to run before lunch.

1308
01:59:48,432 --> 01:59:51,142
- Go ahead, Mr. White.
- Where's the handle?

1309
01:59:51,351 --> 01:59:54,604
There is no handle.
You just push the button.

